s to this answer that these speakers will be received by general society as mentally deficient, and so the usage must be discouraged to uphold workplace standards of proper language. Given how these comments are phrased, it's clear enough that this criticism isn't supposed to be just about "da" versus "the", but rather about all of AAVE / "improper" accents without explicitly naming them.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
